President Donald J. Trump and First Lady Melania Trump will be celebrating Independence Day at the White House by hosting a picnic for military families on the South Lawn. In the evening, there will be a fireworks display provided by the National Park Service, which will be enjoyed by both staff and guests. This year, the President and First Lady are excited to extend the celebration to people across the country through a television partnership. The 90-minute program, hosted by the National Park Service and the National Park Foundation, will feature live performances from various musical artists, including Sara Evans, pianist Lola Astanova, and former American Idol finalists Jax and Jonny Brenns. Additionally, there will be performances from "The President's Own" United States Marines Band, The United States Navy Band Sea Chanters, and The United States Air Force Band's Max Impact. The program will start at 8:00 p.m. Eastern Standard Time on the Hallmark Channel. First Lady Melania Trump expressed her delight in welcoming this new addition to the annual White House July 4th celebration, allowing Americans to tune in from their homes and be part of the festivities.